2416					5/10 000	1	500m			Thick	Yes	Wesa	BB722014816_W1		Block Estimates	8	"With so many birds stretched over a significant area, and more or less at the limit of what could be discerned, the flock density varied from 4 to 5.

Important note: I initially estimated the tidal distances visually, which is extremely difficult at this location. However, after reviewing these distances at the end of the survey, I concluded that the tide was not advancing at 100m/15mins, but more likely around 50m/15mins. Working from this basis I estimated that the starting distance was 500m not 1km as visually ""guessed"". As the tide gets closer, it is easier to estimate the distance. Interestingly, working with the 50m/15 mins rate of advance, the closer estimates match nicely."	BB722014816		BB72	Online	09:00:00		Peeps (Non species specific)
